{
  "texts": [
    "They actuate a combination of joints implementing sophisticated control strategies, to face the increase in hardware complexity, and to produce a harmonious gait (Qiu-zhi et al., 2016; Franks et al., 2021; Kalita et al., 2021).",
    "Within the realm of exoskeleton development, AI emerges as a fundamental cornerstone, actively contributing to various functional tasks in exoskeleton-assisted lower-limb robot-aided rehabilitation.",
    "These tasks include Robot Control (RC), Locomotion Classification (LC), Intention Detection (ID), and Human Joints Trajectory Prediction (HJTP).",
    "AI dynamically adapts to the wearer's movements, seamlessly integrating the exoskeleton with the user.",
    "This adaptability enhances responsiveness and underscores the personalized nature of the interaction."
  ]
}